ENTRY       EC 3.4.11.25                Enzyme
NAME        beta-peptidyl aminopeptidase;
            BapA (ambiguous)
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on peptide bonds (peptidases);
            Aminopeptidases
REACTION    Cleaves N-terminal beta-homoamino acids from peptides composed of 2 to 6 amino acids
COMMENT     Sphingosinicella xenopeptidilytica strain 3-2W4 is able to utilize the beta-peptides beta-homoVal-beta-homoAla-beta-homoLeu and beta-homoAla-beta-homoLeu as sole carbon and energy sources [2].
